Package timing

Interface RepeatRunnable

All Known Subinterfaces:
Algorithm<T,​U>
All Known Implementing Classes:
HeapSort, Linear, Log, Quadratic, QuietAlgorithm, Sum
public interface RepeatRunnable
A Runnable whose execution can be repeated, for timing purposes, because a given run may have interference from other activity on a computer.
Author:
roncytron

  • Method Details

    • reset

      void reset​(Ticker ticker)
      Called before each execution of run. This method is used to reset an implementation to the point where it should be timed.
      Parameters:
      ticker - The Ticker to be used for this run

    • run

      void run()
      The actual workload to be performed after reset().
